1
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:29,719
You took a leave of absence.

2
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:35,159
Kong Xiaocan.

3
00:00:36,759 --> 00:00:38,719
You've really grown wings now.

4
00:00:39,799 --> 00:00:42,000
Did you discuss such a big thing with me?

5
00:00:42,759 --> 00:00:45,520
Your major is great for the civil service exams in the future.

6
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:47,079
You were already later than other kids...

7
00:00:47,079 --> 00:00:48,159
...when starting school.

8
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:49,679
You don't cherish such a good opportunity.

9
00:00:49,679 --> 00:00:50,520
What do you want to do?

10
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,759
Can you face yourself?

11
00:00:51,799 --> 00:00:52,880
I'm afraid of letting you down.

12
00:00:54,719 --> 00:00:55,880
You chose the school.

13
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:56,759
You chose the major.

14
00:00:57,079 --> 00:00:57,840
That lousy major.

15
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,000
I don't like it at all.

16
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Besides, what era is this?

17
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,960
It's not like I have to go to college, so what?

18
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,439
I have to do what I like.

19
00:01:03,479 --> 00:01:04,799
It's a good chance for me to really think.

20
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,239
About what I want to do in the future.

21
00:01:06,439 --> 00:01:06,920
Find my future.

22
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:08,239
As long as you go to school properly.

23
00:01:08,239 --> 00:01:09,640
You can do whatever you want in the future.

24
00:01:10,159 --> 00:01:12,200
Did I try to control you when you went to the snow mountain?

25
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,200
What else do you want to do?

26
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,359
Mom, you... calm down first.

27
00:01:14,359 --> 00:01:14,680
Right now...

28
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,079
I'm taking a leave of absence.

29
00:01:16,439 --> 00:01:17,480
It's not dropping out of school.

30
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,799
I'm just a year late.

31
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:20,680
Being a year late gives me time to think.

32
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,079
"I'll reflect a bit." "If you're a year late..."

33
00:01:22,079 --> 00:01:24,439
If you're a year late, you'll fall far behind others.

34
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,519
If I had these conditions back then...

35
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:27,480
You have them now!

36
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:28,439
You have them now!

37
00:01:29,439 --> 00:01:30,719
Not going to school is your regret.

38
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:31,480
Not mine.

39
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,560
Everyone has their own aspirations.

40
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:33,680
You have this opportunity now.

41
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,519
Go fulfill your dream properly.

42
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,280
Go to college properly.

43
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,680
I don't want to affect your mood.

44
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:37,920
This is my own life now.

45
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:38,840
Let me make my own decisions.

46
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,159
Can't I think for myself?

47
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,319
Your own life?

48
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:43,840
I gave birth to you.

49
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,400
What do you mean "your own life"?

50
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,840
But aren't I doing this for both of us?

51
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,799
I'm also doing this for your own good.

52
00:01:47,799 --> 00:01:48,760
I'm your Mom.

53
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,799
I'm also doing this for your own good.

54
00:01:49,959 --> 00:01:51,239
I'm just doing this for your own good.

55
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:52,519
You have to listen to me.

56
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:55,640
Are you guys fighting?

57
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,920
Wei Mingtian, I'm not going over the wrong answers today.

58
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,439
You go back.

59
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,599
You come in. Come in.

60
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,519
You two focus on correcting your mistakes.

61
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,079
Don't mind us.

62
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,879
Kong Xiaocan, do you have to... in front of an outsider...

63
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:03,920
...argue about this matter?

64
00:02:04,079 --> 00:02:04,760
In front of an outsider...

65
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,920
Can you stop being so agitated?

66
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:06,760
Fine.

67
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,480
It's no big deal.

68
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,680
The sky isn't falling, okay?

69
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,639
I can't control you anymore.

70
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,919
Where's the card? Where is it?

71
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:12,840
Give it to me. What are you doing? What are you doing?

72
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,800
Is this the issue?

73
00:02:13,919 --> 00:02:14,840
How is this not the issue?

74
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,759
Let me just tell you one thing.

75
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:17,560
You took a leave of absence just to make money, right?

76
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,719
Is it because I got sick...

77
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:20,120
...and spent all the family's money?

78
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:20,800
Speak up.

79
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:21,960
If you want to go to school...

80
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,879
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

81
00:02:22,879 --> 00:02:24,360
I didn't want this to affect your mood.

82
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,439
I still want you to go to school.

83
00:02:25,439 --> 00:02:26,280
I'm also doing this for your own good.

84
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,400
I want you to become successful.

85
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,159
I want you to be well.

86
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:28,759
Then I'm also doing this for your own good.

87
00:02:28,759 --> 00:02:29,719
I want you to go to school.

88
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:31,360
I'm also doing this for both of us, right?

89
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:33,319
We don't have any financial problems.

90
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,520
You calm down.

91
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,639
How can I calm down? I'm doing this for your own good.

92
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,360
Everyone calm down for a second.

93
00:02:37,719 --> 00:02:38,599
Let's talk things over calmly.

94
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:44,319
Hello? Brother Maizi.

95
00:02:44,319 --> 00:02:45,120
Hello? Who is this?

96
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,840
Looking for a parent.

97
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:01,039
So here's the situation.

98
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,879
If he wants to improve his grades,

99
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,639
he needs to make time to start from the basics.

100
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,879
But with our current curriculum schedule,

101
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,639
he clearly doesn't have enough time.

102
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,120
Yes, Teacher.

103
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,080
You know, well...

104
00:03:16,759 --> 00:03:17,680
Mingtian, this kid...

105
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,520
has special circumstances.

106
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,319
For him right now,

107
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,400
it is indeed the most critical time.

108
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:22,919
Right.

109
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:24,120
Time is money.

110
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:24,439
Right.

111
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:25,879
So,

112
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,840
don't you think this makes sense?

113
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:31,199
All roads lead to Rome.

114
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:33,319
Studying is just one of them.

115
00:03:34,199 --> 00:03:35,199
The main thing is that this kid...

116
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,919
is already in Rome.

117
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:40,680
In... where?

118
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,439
The main purpose of my chat today...

119
00:03:43,439 --> 00:03:44,120
is just this.

120
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,919
Do you think you could...

121
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:49,439
approve another week of leave for the kid?

122
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,479
We need a "Roman Holiday" right now.

123
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:53,759
Teacher.

124
00:03:54,599 --> 00:03:56,439
He is in the final sprint phase.

125
00:03:56,439 --> 00:03:57,159
Yes, yes, yes.

126
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:58,719
I'm talking to you about time,

127
00:03:58,719 --> 00:03:59,800
and you're asking for a holiday for him.

128
00:03:59,879 --> 00:04:00,800
And a "Roman Holiday" at that.

129
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,319
Thank you, thank you, thank you. Thanks for understanding.

130
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:03,800
Excuse me.

131
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,280
I need to take a call.

132
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:06,840
No... Hello? Hello? Mr. Wu.

133
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:14,479
You... you take... hold this tight.

134
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,759
You have to be my witness.

135
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:16,959
I didn't... I didn't accept anything.

136
00:04:17,199 --> 00:04:18,079
What... what kind of guardian is this?

137
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:20,879
He...

138
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,680
He is Brother Maizi.

139
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,480
I told you to find a parent.

140
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,160
You brought me a "brother" from the streets.

141
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,759
Look at his attitude.

142
00:04:28,759 --> 00:04:30,079
Sorry, Teacher. I'm late.

143
00:04:33,959 --> 00:04:35,000
And what is your attitude?

144
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:36,240
Scoring second to last.

145
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,360
And you have the nerve to sit down?

146
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:41,040
No, guard... guardian.

147
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:41,959
Guard... guardians can sit.

148
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,160
Okay.

149
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:45,319
You... you are?

150
00:04:45,319 --> 00:04:46,000
I'm her brother.

151
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:47,920
Also a "brother" from the streets?

152
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,839
Cousin. A real relative.

153
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:53,319
Then I didn't... I didn't mishear just now?

154
00:04:53,319 --> 00:04:55,839
I thought, second place? Is she that good?

155
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,639
Second to last.

156
00:04:59,759 --> 00:05:00,879
I knew it.

157
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:03,920
So there are... there are people who did worse than her?

158
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,240
Keep it up.

159
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,920
Th-this time, we're not here to discuss...

160
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,439
who is last or who is second to last.

161
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:13,720
I wanted to talk to you about...

162
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,639
the scores are out.

163
00:05:15,279 --> 00:05:15,959
This time...

164
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,600
she scored 350 points.

165
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,800
That's not bad.

166
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,920
350 is pretty high.

167
00:05:20,199 --> 00:05:22,199
Our province's vocational college admission line is 351.

168
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:28,040
The main thing is, she can't get into Duxing U with this.

169
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,399
She's short by two... two or three hundred points.

170
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,040
You want to get into Duxing U too?

171
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,279
I'm not taking the exam.

172
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,160
No, you...

173
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,079
Why are you saying such angry things, child?

174
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,519
We brought the guardian here so the school...

175
00:05:37,519 --> 00:05:38,000
isn't it just so we can...

176
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,439
find a solution?

177
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:40,079
Right?

178
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:42,399
And haven't our grades improved a bit?

179
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:42,920
Exactly.

180
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:44,079
Before, you were dead last.

181
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,199
Through your own hard work...

182
00:05:45,199 --> 00:05:45,879
now you're second to last.

183
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:46,360
See?

184
00:05:46,439 --> 00:05:47,360
If you work a little harder...

185
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,639
you'll be third to last, fourth to last.

186
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,920
We take it step by step.

187
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,160
Look how well the teacher put it.

188
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,439
The main purpose of this visit...

189
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:54,000
is to have the guardian's side...

190
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,480
Understood.

191
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,079
play a supervisory role.

192
00:05:56,079 --> 00:05:56,759
Definitely, definitely, Teacher.

193
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,120
We should work together.

194
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:58,639
Right.

195
00:05:58,759 --> 00:05:59,720
What does the child want? Right now...

196
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:00,680
I'm not taking the exam.

197
00:06:00,959 --> 00:06:01,759
I want to drop out of school.

198
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,000
I want to work. I want to make money.

199
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:03,959
I want to support the family myself.

200
00:06:06,319 --> 00:06:07,720
This student makes a good point.

201
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,279
Teacher, everyone has their own path.

202
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:12,519
If she doesn't want to study, don't force it.

203
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,120
How about this? Our Xiaotian dropped out of school too.

204
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,519
Sorry, let me take this call.

205
00:06:19,319 --> 00:06:20,079
Hello? Hello, President Wu.

206
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,399
Call your parents here.

207
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,480
Treating your studies like a joke.

208
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,000
Teacher, I won't drop out of school.

209
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:26,680
I want to take the college entrance exam. I can definitely pass.

210
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,319
That's the right attitude.

211
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,240
I want to drop out of school.

212
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,439
If I can get in...

213
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:31,360
then pigs can fly.

214
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,439
Call your dad here.

215
00:06:34,439 --> 00:06:35,399
My grandpa passed away.

216
00:06:36,079 --> 00:06:37,040
I said her dad.

217
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:37,920
You...

218
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:40,600
What kind of guardians are these?

219
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,000
Boss.

220
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,360
You're hiring here, right?

221
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,439
I don't hire part-timers here.

222
00:06:54,759 --> 00:06:55,480
I need someone long-term.

223
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:56,439
I can work long-term.

224
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,160
You're a student, right?

225
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,079
This work isn't easy.

226
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:02,399
You'll definitely leave after a bit.

227
00:07:02,759 --> 00:07:05,319
Besides, even if you came, I couldn't take you.

228
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,480
You're a student. Studies come first.

229
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:08,759
You still need to study.

230
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,480
Boss, you're so right. You have vision.

231
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:12,879
Miss! Miss!

232
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,639
We're hiring over here.

233
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,279
Look, this fits your age perfectly.

234
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,120
Our salary is 3,500 a month.

235
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,920
Most importantly, there's commission.

236
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:22,120
You've graduated, right?

237
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:24,240
Then you must know how to make spreadsheets and slides.

238
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,720
Here, a college student...

239
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:27,720
...will surely be a store manager in six months.

240
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,360
How about it? Think it over.

241
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,600
Think it over.

242
00:07:30,759 --> 00:07:31,560
Get into college first.

243
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:32,680
You don't even know spreadsheets.

244
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:35,839
Do you see that?

245
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:37,480
College students are everywhere now.

246
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,439
Don't even talk about college students.

247
00:07:38,439 --> 00:07:39,920
Everyone has to struggle to find a job now.

248
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,160
Do you think you can make it without school?

249
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,079
Then what's the point of me studying?

250
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:43,839
My life is already set.

251
00:07:44,079 --> 00:07:44,839
But you're different.

252
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,319
You haven't finished college yet.

253
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:47,319
How will you find a job later?

254
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:47,720
So what?

255
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,920
So going to college is just to find a job?

256
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,680
Of course not.

257
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:51,920
I hope you can have a good life.

258
00:07:52,279 --> 00:07:53,959
What era is this? "A good life"?

259
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,079
I know what a good life is.

260
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:56,360
Everyone's path to success is different.

261
00:07:56,439 --> 00:07:57,199
It doesn't have to be college.

262
00:07:57,279 --> 00:07:58,160
But you're different.

263
00:07:58,439 --> 00:07:59,519
Your priority now is school.

264
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:00,319
So you have to go to school.

265
00:08:00,319 --> 00:08:00,759
Bullshit.

266
00:08:11,639 --> 00:08:12,600
Okay, okay. Come back.

267
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:13,920
Kong Guifang, listen to me.

268
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,680
Let me break it down for you.

269
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,439
Okay, you go now.

270
00:08:17,439 --> 00:08:18,399
No matter which shop you go to.

271
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:18,959
You go work.

272
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:20,240
Starting now, it'll be like this.

273
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,480
For the next ten years, this will be your life.

274
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:21,879
Raising me.

275
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:22,839
And then?

276
00:08:22,839 --> 00:08:23,680
After I get married and have kids...

277
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,759
...you have to earn money and support me, right?

278
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,199
Do you know what happens when you're forty?

279
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,360
You'll get pancreatic cancer again.

280
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,360
That's probably because you pissed me off.

281
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,279
So don't get pissed off by me.

282
00:08:29,279 --> 00:08:30,399
Live for yourself for once, okay?

283
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:32,000
That life of yours is already clear to see.

284
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:32,559
You have another chance.

285
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:33,679
Why not choose again?

286
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,600
Then what about your future?

287
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:35,879
What will happen to your future?

288
00:08:37,399 --> 00:08:38,960
I didn't say I won't go to school.

289
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:40,080
But I just feel...

290
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,159
...now isn't the time for school.

291
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:41,840
Now isn't the time.

292
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,360
When is the time?

293
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:42,840
You tell me.

294
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:43,879
What do you want to do now?

295
00:08:43,879 --> 00:08:44,559
You want to be the death of me?

296
00:08:44,559 --> 00:08:45,320
I want to earn money to support the family.

297
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,000
It used to be Mom earning money for my school.

298
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,559
Now I want to earn money for Mom's school.

299
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,039
Guifang

300
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,240
If you keep watering it

301
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:37,759
it's going to drown

302
00:09:46,159 --> 00:09:46,679
Guifang

303
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:49,840
are you really not taking the exam?

304
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:54,519
Why?

305
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:57,720
Because

306
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:00,879
no money

307
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,399
Xiaocan took a leave of absence to support the family

308
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,759
entirely because of me

309
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:10,399
I can't just for myself

310
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,960
sacrifice his future

311
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:12,519
Do you understand?

312
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,879
Forget it, you definitely don't understand

313
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:18,919
You don't have kids

314
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:22,519
I don't understand what you're saying

315
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,039
I just think

316
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:27,120
it's a pity

317
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:29,960
If it were me

318
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:31,440
no matter what

319
00:10:33,639 --> 00:10:35,039
I would definitely continue school

320
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:39,919
Our Spotlight Entertainment Agency

321
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,240
in this industry

322
00:10:41,519 --> 00:10:43,320
has a great reputation

323
00:10:44,279 --> 00:10:44,799
And you

324
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,919
surely have your own connections

325
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,320
You can ask around

326
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,159
To be honest

327
00:10:51,039 --> 00:10:51,840
Connections? I...

328
00:10:52,399 --> 00:10:53,720
Who is that? I don't know him

329
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,799
Look, sir

330
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,559
let me just ask you

331
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,399
Go ahead

332
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,399
He just stands there

333
00:11:01,399 --> 00:11:02,039
and you give money?

334
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,559
For what?

335
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,200
In this world

336
00:11:05,679 --> 00:11:06,440
there is no lack of beauty

337
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,320
just a lack of eyes to discover it

338
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,039
Look at him

339
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,519
Regular features

340
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,039
tall and thin

341
00:11:14,679 --> 00:11:15,840
with innocent eyes

342
00:11:16,039 --> 00:11:17,639
God is feeding him

343
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,519
How would God know him?

344
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,279
It's his parents who feed him

345
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,240
Yes, yes, you're right, you're right

346
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:24,320
If you are willing

347
00:11:24,919 --> 00:11:25,720
to sign this contract

348
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,440
at the end of every year

349
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:29,679
I'll give you this amount

350
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:35,120
Five thousand? No way

351
00:11:36,919 --> 00:11:38,080
Five thousand

352
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,320
Uncle, you're making this hard for me

353
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:43,639
How about this

354
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:44,720
Ten thousand

355
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,600
Ten thousand, you...

356
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,120
Twenty thousand

357
00:11:47,879 --> 00:11:48,320
Deal

358
00:11:50,559 --> 00:11:51,639
Such a big thing

359
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:53,879
and you don't discuss it with Mingtian's mom

360
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,240
just decided like that?

361
00:11:56,399 --> 00:11:57,080
Alright, alright

362
00:11:57,159 --> 00:11:58,759
It's like a pie falling from the sky

363
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:01,279
I'm suddenly going to the city to be a star

364
00:12:01,399 --> 00:12:02,240
Do I press this or not?

365
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:03,919
No need, no need to press. You keep it

366
00:12:04,039 --> 00:12:04,559
Here's the money

367
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,679
Xiaotian, come, your turn

368
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,000
Come, come press your fingerprint

369
00:12:09,879 --> 00:12:10,159
Come

370
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:12,240
Press your fingerprint

371
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,320
Press it next to your dad's

372
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,519
That twenty thousand is for my dad

373
00:12:16,039 --> 00:12:16,799
I need a separate deal

374
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:19,879
I can go to the big city and work for you

375
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,440
but I want to go to school

376
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:26,919
I want to go to college

377
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:38,639
Okay

378
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:40,679
Bro will send you to college

379
00:12:42,519 --> 00:12:44,240
I don't care about being a star

380
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,600
There's only one thing I want to do

381
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,200
and that is to go to college

382
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,200
Actually, I know

383
00:12:52,519 --> 00:12:54,440
pies don't just fall from the sky for no reason

384
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,960
but that was a rare opportunity

385
00:12:59,559 --> 00:13:01,600
Seizing the chance to do what you want

386
00:13:02,279 --> 00:13:03,399
I think is the most important thing

387
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:06,519
Guifang

388
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,240
what do you think is the most important?

389
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:15,879
It's Xiaocan

390
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,039
That's right

391
00:13:19,919 --> 00:13:20,440
It's Xiaocan

392
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,000
Don't say I didn't warn you

393
00:13:39,639 --> 00:13:40,639
If you don't fix this soon

394
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,600
you might regret it for the rest of your life

395
00:13:50,039 --> 00:13:51,720
What is truly the most important?

396
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,320
Was my choice wrong?

397
00:14:38,039 --> 00:14:38,919
He ran off.

398
00:14:39,759 --> 00:14:40,919
Wages haven't been paid yet.

399
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,639
All that work for nothing.

400
00:15:10,279 --> 00:15:10,679
Coming.

401
00:15:13,639 --> 00:15:14,519
Brother Xiaocan.

402
00:15:18,679 --> 00:15:19,159
Come in.

403
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,200
Studying?

404
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,000
I'm not disturbing you, am I?

405
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:27,720
It's fine.

406
00:15:28,279 --> 00:15:29,600
Read for two hours and still don't get it.

407
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:31,320
Was just about to take a break when you came.

408
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,159
You don't get it but still read for two hours?

409
00:15:33,159 --> 00:15:34,120
I wouldn't last two minutes.

410
00:15:35,399 --> 00:15:36,480
Someone as obedient as you...

411
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,799
...is definitely the type my mom likes.

412
00:15:38,559 --> 00:15:38,919
A son.

413
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:39,639
That kind of son.

414
00:15:40,399 --> 00:15:41,559
My mom would probably like someone like you.

415
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,600
Strong and energetic.

416
00:15:43,879 --> 00:15:44,639
Hardworking.

417
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,840
Full of energy all day long.

418
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:47,720
Unlike me.

419
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,360
Whenever there's work...

420
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,240
...I make excuses to sneak off and study.

421
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,000
My mom says I'm just...

422
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,279
...full of excuses.

423
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,279
Right? See, all moms are the same.

424
00:16:09,399 --> 00:16:10,000
Xiaocan.

425
00:16:12,039 --> 00:16:13,080
Do you want me to

426
00:16:13,559 --> 00:16:14,600
help you talk some sense into Guifang?

427
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:16,320
You really

428
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,200
catch on fast.

429
00:16:19,879 --> 00:16:20,600
Let me put it this way.

430
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:21,960
Take my cousin for example.

431
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,039
She's going through a rebellious phase right now.

432
00:16:24,399 --> 00:16:25,279
As her cousin,

433
00:16:25,879 --> 00:16:26,600
and as her guardian,

434
00:16:26,879 --> 00:16:28,080
at her young age,

435
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,639
she's prone to being a bit rebellious.

436
00:16:29,879 --> 00:16:31,240
Sometimes she just contradicts whatever I say.

437
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,879
I can't really hold it against a kid.

438
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,600
But for people your age,

439
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:36,919
outsiders,

440
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:37,559
wouldn't she be

441
00:16:38,279 --> 00:16:39,200
easier to communicate with?

442
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:40,200
You could understand

443
00:16:41,519 --> 00:16:41,960
each other, right?

444
00:16:42,679 --> 00:16:43,559
As an elder,

445
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:44,679
I just feel like I...

446
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:47,440
should ask you...

447
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:49,120
to help me.

448
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:51,279
Xiaocan.

449
00:16:52,039 --> 00:16:53,000
Then let me ask you one thing.

450
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:55,480
What do you think is the most important,

451
00:16:56,039 --> 00:16:58,440
the single most important thing to you right now?

452
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,080
The most important...

453
00:17:02,279 --> 00:17:03,600
The most important thing...

454
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,240
is my mom, of course.

455
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,240
Come to think of it,

456
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:14,200
Mom seems to have always just looked like a mom.

457
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,599
Wait a second, Mom is coming right away.

458
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:20,000
Be a good boy, Xiaocan.

459
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:22,599
Don't cry, don't cry, don't cry.

460
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:23,400
Don't cry.

461
00:17:23,799 --> 00:17:24,200
Don't cry.

462
00:17:24,799 --> 00:17:26,440
I'll blow on it and the pain will fly away. Don't cry.

463
00:17:28,799 --> 00:17:31,200
Mom, I want to eat ribs.

464
00:17:31,799 --> 00:17:33,200
Mom already cooked for you at home.

465
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,000
We're not eating this.

466
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:34,880
Come on, let's go home.

467
00:17:41,359 --> 00:17:42,599
She has always been busy,

468
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,119
domineering,

469
00:17:45,359 --> 00:17:46,440
the mom who makes the decisions.

470
00:17:46,839 --> 00:17:47,880
I tell you to balance work and rest, and you get physical!

471
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:48,599
You get physical! I tell you to balance work and rest!

472
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:49,880
You're so unreasonable!

473
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:50,799
You evil mom!

474
00:17:51,039 --> 00:17:52,000
Who is an evil mom?

475
00:17:52,599 --> 00:17:54,319
You play games every day! What's going to become of you?

476
00:17:56,359 --> 00:17:57,400
It seems there was only once...

477
00:17:58,599 --> 00:17:59,240
Just that once.

478
00:17:59,839 --> 00:18:01,480
Mom, can you stop pacing?

479
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,440
You're making me dizzy.

480
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:03,880
Look at you, child.

481
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,279
Why aren't you anxious at all?

482
00:18:05,359 --> 00:18:07,000
Li Wai has already received his admission letter.

483
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,440
You didn't fail to get in, did you?

484
00:18:08,799 --> 00:18:09,799
Good for him.

485
00:18:10,279 --> 00:18:11,920
So what if I don't? It's not Tsinghua or Peking U anyway.

486
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,400
But Duxing U is the number one school around here!

487
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,559
You... you're the only one who cares.

488
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:17,720
I don't care.

489
00:18:23,359 --> 00:18:23,920
Thanks.

490
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:26,200
Mom!

491
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,519
It's here!

492
00:18:28,599 --> 00:18:29,359
Is it that big a deal?

493
00:18:32,759 --> 00:18:33,200
Is it?

494
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,160
Yes!

495
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:35,759
Don't tear it!

496
00:18:36,799 --> 00:18:37,960
Admission Letter.

497
00:18:38,839 --> 00:18:40,319
Student Kong Xiaocan,

498
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:42,359
you have been admitted to our university's

499
00:18:42,799 --> 00:18:44,240
School of Public Administration,

500
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:47,640
majoring in Library Science and Information Science,

501
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,160
as a four-year undergraduate student.

502
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:51,920
Okay, okay, Mom, Mom, you don't have to read the whole thing.

503
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,240
I knew you could get in.

504
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:56,039
You got my brains. Smart.

505
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:56,920
Happy now?

506
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:57,799
Feel better now?

507
00:18:59,279 --> 00:19:00,039
You're the only one who cares.

508
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,440
I don't even care.

509
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,000
So what?

510
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,119
This was my regret.

511
00:19:04,559 --> 00:19:05,640
Now that you've got into college,

512
00:19:06,359 --> 00:19:07,240
Mom is content.

513
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,119
Just this once

514
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,319
I think I saw

515
00:19:19,279 --> 00:19:20,759
the real Kong Guifang

516
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,200
The most important thing

517
00:19:29,559 --> 00:19:30,559
is for her to get into college

518
00:19:30,759 --> 00:19:31,240
right?

519
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,200
Getting Guifang into college, right?

520
00:19:33,599 --> 00:19:34,680
You don't need to empathize so much

521
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,240
Your empathy skills are actually pretty good

522
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,200
Alright, that wasn't for nothing

523
00:19:38,279 --> 00:19:39,160
You... you keep watching

524
00:19:40,839 --> 00:19:41,480
Take care, Brother Xiaocan

525
00:19:48,799 --> 00:19:49,160
Guifang

526
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:50,680
You heard everything, right?

527
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:53,640
You're usually such an honest person

528
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,599
Why use schemes now?

529
00:19:55,039 --> 00:19:55,920
I'm home

530
00:19:56,759 --> 00:19:57,880
We eat in twenty minutes

531
00:19:58,319 --> 00:19:58,680
Okay

532
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,279
Anyway, I'm not going back to school

533
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:05,519
Guifang

534
00:20:06,279 --> 00:20:07,480
You're overthinking it

535
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,519
It's just a substitution problem

536
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,079
What do you mean?

537
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,759
You feel you owe Brother Xiaocan

538
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:15,839
He is the most important thing

539
00:20:16,119 --> 00:20:17,079
That's A equals B

540
00:20:17,559 --> 00:20:18,319
Brother Xiaocan thinks

541
00:20:18,319 --> 00:20:19,839
you getting into college is what matters most

542
00:20:20,079 --> 00:20:21,000
That's B equals C

543
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,960
Since A equals B, and B equals C

544
00:20:23,359 --> 00:20:24,319
then A equals C

545
00:20:27,039 --> 00:20:28,200
Which problem are you talking about?

546
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:32,039
I'm saying you are the most important

547
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,640
That's what Brother Xiaocan wants

548
00:21:40,359 --> 00:21:41,440
I'll take a batch down first

549
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:43,160
Just take the important stuff

550
00:21:43,559 --> 00:21:44,039
Hurry up

551
00:21:46,119 --> 00:21:46,559
Who are you?

552
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,079
Is this the...

553
00:21:48,279 --> 00:21:49,440
Jianshen Gym, right?

554
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:50,279
Yes

555
00:21:51,319 --> 00:21:52,319
I'm looking for your boss

556
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:53,839
Are you the boss here?

557
00:21:55,079 --> 00:21:55,680
I'm not

558
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,200
Do I look like it?

559
00:21:58,720 --> 00:21:59,920
Then what are you doing?

560
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:01,640
Renovating? Or running away?

561
00:22:04,559 --> 00:22:05,640
Probably running away

562
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:06,799
Look at the state of this place

563
00:22:07,319 --> 00:22:07,799
Boss

564
00:22:08,839 --> 00:22:09,359
Hurry it up

565
00:22:09,839 --> 00:22:10,640
Or else the members

566
00:22:10,799 --> 00:22:12,160
and Kong Xiaocan will come for their money

567
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:12,759
Quick

568
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,000
Who is it?

569
00:22:18,519 --> 00:22:19,119
The cleaner?

570
00:22:22,119 --> 00:22:24,119
I'm the one here to collect for Kong Xiaocan

571
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:52,880
Mom

572
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,519
Pay me back. You set me up.

573
00:22:54,799 --> 00:22:55,920
Mom, Mom, Mom!

574
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,759
Alright, alright, alright.

575
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,039
So I understand now.

576
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:05,799
Let me get this straight.

577
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:09,119
You and she are a couple.

578
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:11,759
Not anymore.

579
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:18,000
And you and he are also a couple.

580
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,480
He's my pet.

581
00:23:22,559 --> 00:23:24,240
So you two are...

582
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:24,880
She's my client.

583
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:25,759
Love rivals.

584
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:32,480
And who are you?

585
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:35,200
I'm mostly with him...

586
00:23:36,359 --> 00:23:38,119
That is, one of her employees.

587
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:39,880
Ex-employee.

588
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:40,799
Ex-boss.

589
00:23:43,039 --> 00:23:44,519
So you hit her.

590
00:23:44,519 --> 00:23:46,160
So you two are...

591
00:23:46,279 --> 00:23:47,680
What are you thinking? I don't know him.

592
00:23:48,079 --> 00:23:49,359
Those two scammed him out of money.

593
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,640
Then you two must be...

594
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,319
I'm his guardian.

595
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,119
So I understand now.

596
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,200
Let me get this straight.

597
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:06,799
You and she are a couple.

598
00:24:07,759 --> 00:24:08,680
Not anymore.

599
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:09,359
No, not a couple.

600
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:11,920
So you two...

601
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:12,440
Pet.

602
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:13,960
Right, pet.

603
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:14,559
I'm her employee.

604
00:24:14,559 --> 00:24:15,119
I... Right.

605
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,200
Guardian. Ex-employee.

606
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,000
Right.

607
00:24:18,759 --> 00:24:20,759
Mom just doesn't want you to sacrifice anything for me.

608
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:22,359
Even if you think...

609
00:24:22,359 --> 00:24:23,599
something like taking a leave of absence for a year...

610
00:24:23,599 --> 00:24:25,400
to Mom, that's a huge deal.

611
00:24:26,359 --> 00:24:26,720
Wait a minute.

612
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:30,160
What you can do for me, I can't do for you?

613
00:24:30,279 --> 00:24:31,119
When you do it, it's duty.

614
00:24:31,119 --> 00:24:32,000
When I do it, it's a sacrifice.

615
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:32,880
Why the double standard?

616
00:24:35,079 --> 00:24:35,400
Yes.

617
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,200
I really do want to go to college.

618
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,799
Especially, I want to go to college with you.

619
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:41,000
I want to... with you...

620
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,240
walk through those campus gates.

621
00:24:42,279 --> 00:24:42,559
But...

622
00:24:42,559 --> 00:24:43,279
You're afraid you won't pass.

623
00:24:43,759 --> 00:24:44,680
And have to repeat the year next year.

624
00:24:45,119 --> 00:24:46,319
And I insisted on taking a leave of absence for a year.

625
00:24:46,319 --> 00:24:47,200
You feel like you've held me back.

626
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,079
Another sacrifice, right?

627
00:24:48,559 --> 00:24:50,200
Mom, Mom, Mom. Oh my Mom.

628
00:24:50,279 --> 00:24:51,160
I'm going to test you when we get back.

629
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,400
See what your MBTI personality is.

630
00:24:52,599 --> 00:24:53,440
You overthink so much.

631
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:54,559
If you had this energy...

632
00:24:54,559 --> 00:24:55,440
you would have passed physics long ago.

633
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:56,039
Bullshit.

634
00:24:56,319 --> 00:24:57,640
Don't you know how hard physics is?

635
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:58,680
Did you ever pass it yourself?

636
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,119
Everyone has their specialty.

637
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,319
I was a liberal arts student.

638
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,119
No, Mom.

639
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:06,000
Look at these past few months.

640
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,759
You've stuck with it.

641
00:25:08,319 --> 00:25:09,480
Although I'm unreliable...

642
00:25:09,839 --> 00:25:11,599
I really don't want to give up halfway on this.

643
00:25:12,279 --> 00:25:13,559
Plus, you've become young now.

644
00:25:13,559 --> 00:25:14,839
Your physical fitness is better than mine.

645
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,039
You've restarted your life.

646
00:25:16,039 --> 00:25:17,480
Shouldn't you do something you want to do?

647
00:25:25,119 --> 00:25:25,880
Then let's make a bet.

648
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:27,079
Kong Xiaocan, do you dare?

649
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:28,400
Is there anything your son doesn't dare to do?

650
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:30,839
One month.

651
00:25:32,039 --> 00:25:33,039
Just one month's time.

652
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,440
I'll score 500 points this month.

653
00:25:35,559 --> 00:25:36,160
You go find a...

654
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:37,319
job that earns five thousand a month.

655
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,319
If we fail even one of these two conditions...

656
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:41,000
Then we both go back to our places.

657
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:41,640
And do our own things.

658
00:25:41,799 --> 00:25:42,279
Is that a deal?

659
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:48,000
Okay.

660
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,359
Is three thousand a month okay?

661
00:25:50,039 --> 00:25:51,640
Okay, okay, okay. Five thousand it is. Five thousand.

662
00:25:52,319 --> 00:25:52,680
Deal.

663
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:17,920
Find a reliable job.

664
00:26:18,039 --> 00:26:19,039
Support my Mom through college.

665
00:26:19,039 --> 00:26:20,240
This is what's most important.

666
00:26:20,319 --> 00:26:22,279
Everything else needs to step aside.

667
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:26,599
Kong Xiaocan, you don't have the energy to think about anything else right now.

668
00:26:55,839 --> 00:26:57,240
Partners Wanted

669
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,000
Five Social Insurances and One Housing Fund

670
00:26:59,799 --> 00:27:00,759
Salary negotiable

671
00:27:19,039 --> 00:27:19,920
Hello, excuse me.

672
00:27:20,839 --> 00:27:21,200
Hello.

673
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,119
You've been looking at it for half an hour.

674
00:27:30,839 --> 00:27:32,079
Is there a character you don't recognize?

675
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,559
Or do you not recognize any of them?

676
00:27:34,519 --> 00:27:36,599
I know the characters well enough.

677
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:40,480
It's just that some things don't make sense.

678
00:27:41,119 --> 00:27:41,599
How so?

679
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:43,920
Why is the base salary here...

680
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:45,480
...five hundred higher than normal?

681
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,640
And there are weekends off and comp time every week.

682
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:48,559
Plus you pay the Five Social Insurances and One Housing Fund.

683
00:27:49,839 --> 00:27:50,920
You can also choose not to have them.

684
00:27:52,359 --> 00:27:53,319
No, I want them, I want them.

685
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:56,160
It's just... this windfall is too overwhelming.

686
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:59,160
But there is one thing.

687
00:27:59,759 --> 00:28:00,599
I'd like to discuss with you.

688
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,640
Can the probation period...

689
00:28:03,039 --> 00:28:04,440
...be changed from two weeks to one?

690
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,359
Because I really need money urgently.

691
00:28:09,119 --> 00:28:09,720
Okay. If not...

692
00:28:11,039 --> 00:28:13,400
From this moment on, consider yourself hired.

693
00:28:14,599 --> 00:28:15,720
No back-and-forth negotiation? Come on.

694
00:28:16,599 --> 00:28:17,279
Drink this tea.

695
00:28:18,799 --> 00:28:19,400
I'll down one.

696
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:21,920
Join me to admire the rain.

697
00:28:23,039 --> 00:28:24,839
It's not easy for you young people.

698
00:28:25,359 --> 00:28:27,519
Let me tell you about my business philosophy.

699
00:28:28,359 --> 00:28:28,880
One word.

700
00:28:29,279 --> 00:28:30,000
Happiness.

701
00:29:17,759 --> 00:29:18,319
Xuefan.

702
00:29:19,119 --> 00:29:19,559
Look.

703
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,279
On this mock exam...

704
00:29:21,279 --> 00:29:22,720
...you scored over 660 points.

705
00:29:23,039 --> 00:29:24,039
You got a perfect score in math.

706
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:25,079
Could you...

707
00:29:25,359 --> 00:29:26,480
...explain the questions to us?

708
00:29:27,279 --> 00:29:29,240
This is the only favor Auntie asks of you.

709
00:29:29,519 --> 00:29:31,079
Wait, who are you calling Auntie?

710
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:33,640
I... I've just been retaking the exam for two years.

711
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:34,599
And you call me Auntie?

712
00:29:34,599 --> 00:29:35,079
No, no.

713
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,039
Don't be like that.

714
00:29:36,039 --> 00:29:36,680
That's not what I meant.

715
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,960
My schedule is actually quite tight.

716
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:39,359
Please help us.

717
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:42,079
Please.

718
00:29:47,519 --> 00:29:49,200
I can still squeeze out some time.

719
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:50,599
Thank you, thank you.

720
00:29:50,599 --> 00:29:51,079
That's great.

721
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:51,680
Thank you so much.

722
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:52,279
Thank you, thank you.

723
00:29:53,119 --> 00:29:54,240
Your foundation is weak.

724
00:29:54,599 --> 00:29:56,880
Do this first to strengthen your basics.

725
00:29:57,039 --> 00:29:58,279
Give it to me after you finish.

726
00:29:58,279 --> 00:29:59,000
I'll explain it to you.

727
00:29:59,079 --> 00:29:59,400
Okay.

728
00:30:00,519 --> 00:30:01,400
You, come here.

729
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:04,119
I'll explain this paper to you one-on-one.

730
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:05,240
Five hundred points.

731
00:30:05,559 --> 00:30:06,640
Kong Guifang, charge!

732
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:15,279
Mom.

733
00:30:16,039 --> 00:30:17,279
Congratulations on breaking 400 points.

734
00:30:17,359 --> 00:30:18,240
I'm adding a chicken leg to your meal today.

735
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:19,519
Quick, it's freshly stewed.

736
00:30:19,519 --> 00:30:20,319
Super, super fragrant. Tender. Take it.

737
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:21,039
I haven't finished the questions yet.

738
00:30:21,039 --> 00:30:22,240
You... eat first, then write.

739
00:30:22,319 --> 00:30:23,519
Questions aren't done... Quick, it's chicken leg freedom.

740
00:30:23,519 --> 00:30:25,079
Be my Chicken Leg Girl today. It's a must.

741
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:25,880
Be good, eat.

742
00:30:26,799 --> 00:30:27,839
Okay, I got it. You leave, hurry up.

743
00:30:27,839 --> 00:30:28,359
You must eat it.

744
00:30:30,119 --> 00:30:31,160
Look, I'm just... Am I eating?

745
00:30:32,119 --> 00:30:32,519
Eat it.

746
00:30:32,799 --> 00:30:33,680
I know, I know.

747
00:30:36,079 --> 00:30:36,519
I just kn...

748
00:30:38,079 --> 00:30:38,519
What are you doing?

749
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,440
Eat. Eat first.

750
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,240
Eat, eat, eat.

751
00:31:24,079 --> 00:31:26,000
Can you let me play for a couple of days?

752
00:31:26,319 --> 00:31:27,960
I'm about to go crazy from studying.

753
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:29,599
Oh, give it a rest.

754
00:31:30,759 --> 00:31:31,880
You're about to take the exam.

755
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,200
Don't you have a clue?

756
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,480
And you say you're studying like crazy.

757
00:31:34,599 --> 00:31:35,799
If you don't study now, when will you?

758
00:31:36,119 --> 00:31:37,039
Come on, right now.

759
00:31:37,039 --> 00:31:38,519
Just find me one person who went crazy from studying.

760
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:40,160
And I'll let you play for a week.

761
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,119
This child...

762
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:00,319
Guifang

763
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,079
We've finished memorizing all this.

764
00:32:02,599 --> 00:32:03,160
Let's go over there.

765
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,000
We haven't memorized that part yet. Let's go.

766
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:04,599
Let's go.

767
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:08,480
Mom, look, there are two study maniacs here.

768
00:32:08,799 --> 00:32:10,680
Does this mean we can play for two weeks?

769
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:15,480
Dong Xuefan

770
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:17,680
Ninety-six points

771
00:32:21,079 --> 00:32:21,960
Kong Guifang

772
00:32:22,799 --> 00:32:23,519
Seventy-three points

773
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:28,319
Wei Mingtian

774
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:30,000
Sixty-eight points

775
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:40,640
Xiaocan

776
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:42,599
Xiaocan

777
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:45,880
Where is he?

778
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:49,039
I'm back.

779
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:50,559
What are you doing?

780
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:52,319
I was just about to... Why did you take the quilt out?

781
00:32:52,319 --> 00:32:52,880
I was just telling you.

782
00:32:53,359 --> 00:32:53,920
What is it?

783
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:55,720
Starting today...

784
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:56,920
Starting today...

785
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,519
Starting today, you're living here.

786
00:32:58,680 --> 00:32:59,640
I've got everything ready for you.

787
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:01,319
Aromatherapy, flowers, and stuff.

788
00:33:01,319 --> 00:33:02,559
It's quiet here, so you can focus on exam prep.

789
00:33:05,359 --> 00:33:06,079
You're so thoughtful.

790
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:07,519
I'm your cousin now, after all.

791
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:08,599
Of course.

792
00:33:09,839 --> 00:33:10,160
By the way.

793
00:33:10,640 --> 00:33:11,039
Here.

794
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:12,680
Look at this.

795
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:13,400
What is this?

796
00:33:13,519 --> 00:33:14,000
What is it?

797
00:33:14,680 --> 00:33:15,000
This...

798
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:16,720
What's the total score?

799
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,440
Five hundred and eight.

800
00:33:21,319 --> 00:33:21,759
For real?

801
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:25,799
You're amazing, Mom.

802
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:28,200
Are you serious? 508 is enough for Duxing U.

803
00:33:29,799 --> 00:33:30,720
Don't rush, let me tell you.

804
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:31,720
I performed better than usual.

805
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:35,000
Let me tell you.

806
00:33:36,279 --> 00:33:38,200
Now we're both in the "five" club.

807
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,240
Look, my salary came in. See for yourself.

808
00:33:44,319 --> 00:33:44,839
Not bad, right?

809
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:50,079
I'm telling you, today is a double celebration.

810
00:33:50,079 --> 00:33:51,599
We have to go have a big feast.

811
00:33:51,599 --> 00:33:52,799
Let's eat whatever we want. Let's go.

812
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:53,400
Don't.

813
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:54,680
Don't get carried away.

814
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:55,640
This five thousand yuan...

815
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:56,680
...was hard-earned.

816
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:57,599
You have to save the money.

817
00:33:57,599 --> 00:33:58,000
You know?

818
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:58,839
You can't spend it all at once.

819
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,119
You won't miss this little bit.

820
00:34:00,119 --> 00:34:01,039
Today is such a great day.

821
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:01,559
I got 508.

822
00:34:01,559 --> 00:34:02,160
It is a good day.

823
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:02,799
No.

824
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,680
Since it's a good day, I'll cook a meal to celebrate.

825
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:05,759
Don't. We eat that every day, I'm sick of it.

826
00:34:05,759 --> 00:34:06,799
I've already ordered takeout.

827
00:34:06,799 --> 00:34:07,480
Why did you order takeout?

828
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,880
Cancel it for me, I'll cook.

829
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:10,480
The rider has already picked up the order.

830
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:11,480
That's... that's not nice to them.

831
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,360
It's irresponsible to the rider.

832
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:13,480
I'm about to wash the rice.

833
00:34:13,519 --> 00:34:14,679
If you wash rice, I'll unplug the power.

834
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:21,599
Actually, the teachers called your parents here...

835
00:34:22,639 --> 00:34:24,320
...not to have them come over...

836
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:25,760
...to vent their emotions...

837
00:34:26,719 --> 00:34:28,400
...or to let your parents blame you.

838
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,079
Yes, yes, yes.

839
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:33,000
Kids these days really have it tough.

840
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:36,480
We...

841
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:38,360
...want to work with your parents...

842
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:40,119
...to find your problems together...

843
00:34:40,119 --> 00:34:41,280
...and help you solve them.

844
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:42,000
Right.

845
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,000
Kids these days...

846
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:45,000
...suffer a lot.

847
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:49,679
Kids these days really don't have it easy.

848
00:34:52,559 --> 00:34:53,039
Tell me...

849
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:56,000
Parents were all once children themselves.

850
00:34:56,519 --> 00:34:58,519
They should understand children's thoughts best.

851
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,880
But instead, they keep...

852
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:02,960
...criticizing the kids for this and that.

853
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:05,360
Saying that once you become parents later...

854
00:35:05,559 --> 00:35:07,519
...you will understand our way of thinking.

855
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:09,920
Well, the kid really hasn't been a parent.

856
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:13,199
But you have been a child.

857
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:15,320
Right?

858
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:17,199
Right.

859
00:35:18,039 --> 00:35:18,320
Right.

860
00:35:19,679 --> 00:35:20,840
I hope you can understand that too.
